{# patterns_mod.rs.tera — renders src/patterns/mod.rs from pattern_index.rq.

   Emits, by iterating rows ordered by id: (1) `pub mod <name>;` declarations, (2)
   `pub use <name>::<name>;` re-exports, and (3) the `PATTERN_REGISTRY` slice of PatternSpec.
   Object kinds arrive as parallel comma-joined `row.objectCodes` / `row.objectNames`; the
   `zip`/`split` Tera helpers below expand them into `ObjectKind { code, name }` literals.
   The output carries the GENERATED banner; the committed mod.rs is the offline source of
   truth.

   Implementation note on `| trim`:
   SPARQL serialisers may emit comma-separated values with surrounding whitespace
   (e.g. `"1, 2, 3"` rather than `"1,2,3"`).  Each element is passed through `| trim`
   after splitting so that stray spaces do not leak into generated integer literals or
   string constants, which would cause compile errors or silent mismatches.
#}
